  "texts": [
    "Our objective is to derive a Fokker-Planck-type equation that describes the evolution of the rescaled distribution f (t, A, w).",
    "Since the calculations are cumbersome, for the sake of clarity we only sketch them in the case of agent-agent interactions (the interactions with the leaders can be treated in the exact same way).",
    "First, we Taylor expand the terms encoding the binary interaction in (2), to recoverφ(A ′, w ′) -φ(A, w) = ∂ w φ(A, w)(w ′ -w) + ∂ A φ(A, w)(A ′ -A) + 1 2 ∂ 2 w φ(A, w)(w ′ -w) 2 + ∂ 2 wA φ(A, w)(A ′ -A)(w ′ -w) + 1 2 ∂ 2 A φ(A, w)(A ′ -A) + R ϵ (A, A ′, w, w ′),where R ϵ (A, A ′, w, w ′) denotes the remainder of the expansion.",
    "Hence, we can rewrite (11) asd dt ∫ R×I φ(A, w)f (t, A, w)dAdw = 1 ϵ ∫ R 2 ×I 2 ∂ w φ(A, w) ⟨w ′ -w⟩ f (t, A, w)f (t, B, v)dAdBdwdv + 1 ϵ ∫ R 2 ×I 2 ∂ A φ(A, w) ⟨A ′ -A⟩ f (t, A, w)f (t, B, v)dAdBdwdv + 1 2ϵ ∫ R 2 ×I 2 ∂ 2 w φ(A, w) ⟨(w ′ -w) 2 ⟩ f (t, A, w)f (t, B, v)dAdBdwdv + 1 ϵ ∫ R 2 ×I 2 ∂ 2 wA φ(A, w) ⟨(A ′ -A)(w ′ -w)⟩ f (t, A, w)f (t, B, v)dAdBdwdv + 1 2ϵ ∫ R 2 ×I 2 ∂ 2 A φ(A, w) ⟨(A ′ -A) 2 ⟩ f (t, A, w)f (t, B, v)dAdBdwdv + 1 ϵ ∫ R 2 ×I 2 R ϵ (A, A ′, w, w ′)f (t, A, w)f (t, B, v)dAdBdwdv.Next, we use (2) to substitute the expressions for w ′ and A ′ and we compute the means of the random variables to cancel out some terms, recalling that ⟨η p ⟩ = 0.",
    "Then, taking the limit ϵ → 0, additional terms cancel out if one assumes in particular ⟨|η p | 3 ⟩ < +∞, so that [10, 34]1 ϵ ∫ R 2 ×I 2 R ε (A, A ′, w, w ′)f (t, A, w)f (t, B, v)dAdBdwdv → ϵ→0 0.Finally, assuming no-flux boundary conditions and integrating back by parts in order to get rid of the derivatives of φ(A, w) (after repeating the same calculations for the interactions with the leaders), we formally obtain a Fokker-Planck-type equation describing the evolution of f (t, A, w) [10,28,29,34], of the form∂ t f (t, A, w) = Q p (f, f)(t, A, w) + Q ℓ (f, f ℓ)(t, A, w),(13)whereQ p (f, f)(t, A, w) = σ 2 p 2 ∂ 2 w (D 2 (w)f (t, A, w)) + λ p ( Āω p + ε)∂ w (K[f](t, w)f (t, A, w)) -λ A ∂ A (( Āω p + ε -a p)f (t, A, w))(14)is the collisional operator related to the interactions inside the population, whileQ ℓ (f, f ℓ)(t, A, w) = σ 2 ℓ 2 ∂ 2 w (D 2 (w)f (t, A, w)) + λ ℓ ( Āω ℓ + ε)∂ w (J [f ℓ](w)f (t, A, w)) -λ A ∂ A (( Āω ℓ + ε -a ℓ)f (t, A, w)),(15)is the collisional operator related to the interactions agent-leaders."
